course.subject: BTRY
course.course_title: Graduate Special Topics in Biometry and Statistics

notes.note: Prerequisite: BTRY 3080, 6010 and 6020, or equivalents. This class is designed for PhD students in statistics, applied mathematics, and mathematical biology, and will be adapted to the background of students enrolled. It assumes knowledge of probability and at least the basic ideas behind statistical inference. There is an expectation that students will be able to write and use programs in R or Matlab.
